\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. S. altissima} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 600 (1753). Stems up to 100 cm, erect, simple or branched. Leaves 5-15 × 2-5 cm, ovate, serrate, glabrous or hairy beneath on the veins. Internodes of inflorescence 10-12 mm. Bracts 6-10 mm, shorter than the flowers, ovate to ovate-lanceolate, entire, acute, green. Calyx without or with only a few long, white, eglandular hairs. Corolla 12-16(-18) mm, bluish; lower lip whitish; tube subglabrous to pubescent outside.{\i  Woods. E.C. & S.E. Europe; C. & S. Italy.} Al Bu Cz Gr Hu It Ju Rm Rs (C, W, K) [Au Be Br Ga Ge].
