\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. S. albida} L., {\i Mantissa Alt.} 248 (1771) (incl.{\i  S. pallida }Bieb.,{\i  S. woronowii} Juz.). Stems 15-30(-40) cm, more or less erect, usually branched, with short appressed eglandular hairs. Leaves 2-3 cm, triangular to deltate, crenate, more or less obtuse, pubescent to velutinous. Internodes of inflorescence c. 10 mm. Bracts 10-12 mm, shorter than flowers, ovate to ovate-lanceolate, entire, green. Corolla (10-)12-16 mm, white.{\i  Rocky places. S.E. Europe.} Bu Gr It Ju Rm Rs (K) Tu [Ga].
